snippet: Falling concrete pinned drivers in their vehicles and started a fire in the tunnel  in eastern Japan, severing a major highway leading to Tokyo.
abstract: Nine people are found dead after their cars were crushed by slabs of concrete that fell from ceiling of tunnel in eastern Japan, severing major highway leading to Tokyo; police are investigating cause of collapse of three-mile passage and for evidence of negligence by company that operates highway.
lead_paragraph: Falling concrete pinned drivers in their vehicles and started a fire in the tunnel  in eastern Japan, severing a major highway leading to Tokyo.

headline.seo: Tunnel Collapses Outside Tokyo Kills Nine
headline.main: Nine Killed When Highway Tunnel Collapses in Japan
headline.print_headline: Nine Killed When Highway Tunnel Collapses in Japan
